title: fanoutqa: Which of the main actors from the movie “The Avengers” have won Academy Awards? (29242cc91b49e88e)

chat_history.content: Which of the main actors from the movie “The Avengers” have won Academy Awards?

The Avengers had an all-star cast, so you'd be right to assume that some of the actors have won Academy Awards.

- Jeremy Renner, who played Hawkeye, won an Academy Award for Best Actor in a Supporting Role for his performance in the movie Hurt Locker.
- Scarlett Johansson, who played Black Widow, won an Academy Award for Best Supporting Actress for her performance in the movie Jojo Rabbit.
- Anthony Hopkins, who played Odin in Thor and Thor: The Dark World, has won two Academy Awards for Best Actor in a Leading Role, the first for his role in The Silence of the Lambs and the second for his role in The Father.

Whilst not technically a main character, another actor from the Marvel Cinematic Universe is also an Academy Award winner:
- Mahershala Ali, who plays Blade in the upcoming movie of the same name, has won two Academy Awards for Best Supporting Actor, the first for his role in Moonlight, and the second for his role in Green Book.
